# File and Module Organization

- `bot.py` wires DI and starts the Telegram bot.
- `app/` contains core packages: adapters (`telegram/`, `content/`, `youtube/`, `openrouter/`, `external/`), `core/` utilities (URL normalization, summary contract, logging), `db/` (SQLite + Peewee models), `agents/`, `cli/`, `api/` (FastAPI mobile endpoints), `services/`, `domain/`, and `prompts/`.
- `SPEC.md` and `.docs/` are the canonical references for architecture, requirements, tests, and ADRs.
- `tests/` holds unit/integration/E2E tests (pytest + pytest-asyncio).
- `Dockerfile` builds the runtime image; persistent data (SQLite, downloads) live under `/data`.
- Keep business logic separated from transport layers (Telegram, FastAPI, CLI).
